DSA-2018-011: RSA Identity Governance and Lifecycle Privilege Escalation Vulnerability

Dell EMC Identifier:  DSA-2018-011


CVE Identifier:  CVE-2018-1182


Severity:  High

 
Severity Rating:  CVSSv3 Base Score: 7.8 /AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H
 

Affected Products:

RSA Identity Governance and Lifecycle versions 7.0.1, 7.0.2, all patch levels (hardware appliance and software bundle deployments only).

RSA Via Lifecycle and Governance version 7.0, all patch levels (hardware appliance and software bundle deployments only)

RSA Identity Management & Governance (RSA IMG) versions 6.9.0, 6.9.1, all patch levels (hardware appliance and software bundle deployments only)
 

Summary:

RSA Identity Governance and Lifecycle, RSA Via Lifecycle and Governance, and RSA IMG contain fixes for a privilege escalation vulnerability that could potentially be exploited by malicious users to compromise an affected system.

 

Details:

The privilege escalation vulnerability in RSA Identity Governance and Lifecycle, RSA Via Lifecycle and Governance, and RSA IMG product appliance allows certain OS level users to execute arbitrary scripts with root level privileges

 

Recommendation:

The following RSA Identity Governance and Lifecycle, RSA Via Lifecycle and Governance, and RSA IMG releases contain resolutions to this vulnerability (fix is required for hardware and software appliances only):

 

        RSA Identity Governance and Lifecycle 7.0.2:   7.0.2, P05 or later
        RSA Identity Governance and Lifecycle 7.0.1:  Hot Fix available for P05
        RSA Via L&G 7.0: Requires upgrading to 7.0.2, P05 or later
        RSA IMG v6.9.1: Requires upgrading to 7.0.2, P05 or later
 

Customers can obtain the documentation and software for these releases by downloading them from the Downloads area on the RSA Identity Governance and Lifecycle space of RSA Link.

 

RSA recommends all customers upgrade at the earliest opportunity.

 

For additional documentation, downloads, and more, visit the RSA Identity Governance & Lifecycle page on RSA Link.

 

Severity Rating:
For an explanation of Severity Ratings, refer to the Security Advisories Severity Rating knowledge base article. RSA recommends all customers take into account both the base score and any relevant temporal and environmental scores which may impact the potential severity associated with particular security vulnerability.

 

EOPS Policy:

RSA has a defined End of Primary Support policy associated with all major versions. Please refer to the Product Version Life Cycle for additional details.

 

RSA Link Security Advisories:
